Comment.value:
when selected by the person he gave the ring to

plot not completed

the "Evaine_Plot" global is set as follows:
0 = plot not completed
5 = PC has agreed to kill Baram in exchange for Evaine
6 = PC has not agreed to kill Baram, but knows Kurth has Evaine
9 = Kurth reneged on his deal to release Evaine
10 = Evaine found in Kurth's bedroom but not brought yet
50 = Evaine killed
100 = Evaine rescued (this is set by a trigger at the entrance to the area)
200 = Elynwyd is leaving

plot not done
he has not given away the ring

the "Evaine_Plot" global is set as follows:
0 = plot not completed
5 = PC has agreed to kill Baram in exchange for Evaine
6 = PC has not agreed to kill Baram, but knows Kurth has Evaine
9 = Kurth reneged on his deal to release Evaine
10 = Evaine found in Kurth's bedroom but not brought yet
50 = Evaine killed
100 = Evaine rescued (this is set by a trigger at the entrance to the area)
200 = Elynwyd is leaving
speaker is not a fighter type but has charisma of 10+
speaker is a fighter class AND has more than 9 charisma

alternatively, this information could be more vague, as in a 'general area' the party has to search
OR the rescue plot giver could direct the PC to someone who might know more
either way, this information is only given to a PC who has accepted the plot, not on this response
